# ── Private / do-not-publish content (CRITICAL for the cloud-migration commit) ──
# When the git root moves from site/ up to here, `git add -A` would otherwise
# sweep these into a PUBLIC repo. Review `git status` before the first commit.
# NOTE: .gitignore does NOT support inline (trailing) comments — keep patterns
# on their own lines, or they silently match nothing.
# full book manuscript — the product being sold; keep private:
cbtcbook/
# third-party reference PDFs (copyright) — never publish:
cbtcreference/

# Earlier-session git backups
.git-*
*.lock

# Secrets — never commit
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem

# OS / Editor
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Node (Astro project)
node_modules/
dist/
.astro/

# Build artifacts
*.log
last-run.log

# ── Internal docs / strategy — keep out of the public repo ──
# Handoffs and operations contain identity-management strategy, anti-spam tactics, internal voice rules.
HANDOFF.md
BLOG_OPERATIONS.md
AGENTS.md
SESSION_LOG_*.md
# Blog production planning + agent reference (SEO/content strategy, forbidden phrases, term lists).
cbtcbook-blog-PLAN.md
cbtcbook-blog-100-articles.md
cbtcbook-blog-glossary.md
# Agent QA reports + image-todo notes; live in blog-drafts/ next to the article .md files.
blog-drafts/_*.md
# Personal / belongs-elsewhere singletons.
github-profile-README.md
orcid-import.bib

# ── Large directories not used by the cloud build ──
pptx/
codex-video-lab/
